The paper proposes a fully data-driven generative dialogue system for knowledge grounded conversation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. Additionally, the paper involves the use of knowledge bases and domain-specific knowledge, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of dynamic knowledge enquirer, which involves information retrieval techniques, indicating the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method on datasets, which suggests the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
